Sure, I can help you with that. To create a simple gaming website, you need to have a basic understanding of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below is a basic example to get you started:

HTML: This will define the structure of your website.
CSS: This will style your website to make it look appealing.
JavaScript: This will add interactivity to your website.
Here is a basic example:

1. HTML (index.html)
HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Gaming Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to the Gaming Website</h1>
        <nav>
            <a href="#">Home</a>
            <a href="#">Games</a>
            <a href="#">About</a>
            <a href="#">Contact</a>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="game">
            <h2>Game 1: Tic-Tac-Toe</h2>
            <div id="tic-tac-toe">
                <!-- Tic-Tac-Toe game will be inserted here by JavaScript -->
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 Gaming Website</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
 Public code references from 3 repositories
2. CSS (styles.css)
CSS
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    color: #333;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
}

nav a {
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
}

main {
    padding: 2rem;
}

.game {
    background-color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-radius: 5px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    position: fixed;
    width: 100%;
    bottom: 0;
}
